delete_path_category(25.10)                        delete_path_category(25.10)

Name
       delete_path_category - Deletes the names of the selected categories

Syntax
       delete_path_category

       [-help]

       <category_name>

       Deletes the names of the selected categories.

       The command can be applied when categories are created in Global Timing
       Debug.

       For  more information, see the Debugging Timing Results chapter of User
       Guide.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each delete_path_category parameter.

              For  a  detailed  description of the command and all its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man delete_path_category

       <category_name>
              Specifies the name of the category that is needed to be deleted.

Example
       The following command deletes the category worst_paths:

       delete_path_category worst_paths

Related Information
       The Timing Budgeting chapter of the Innovus User Guide document.

